{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775866725390,"sessionID":"ses_28618bf6dffeGAxAQ8WcrcDRZ1","part":{"id":"prt_d79e7b97f001GEgg46YeNnhsCD","messageID":"msg_d79e7ad61001bwSu4GWDEIAlfy","sessionID":"ses_28618bf6dffeGAxAQ8WcrcDRZ1","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_f68779df633c4aceb0e8fd7a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-017/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-017/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-017 — PicoD JWT Middleware Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/picod` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | S |\n11: | Stage | ST-3 completed |\n12: \n13: ## Atomic Tasks\n14: \n15: ### Phase 1: RSA Key Handling (`crypto.go`)\n16: \n17: - [ ] **TASK-001**: Create `pkg/picod/crypto.go`\n18:   - Define package-level imports: `crypto/rsa`, `crypto/x509`, `encoding/pem`, `encoding/base64`\n19: \n20: - [ ] **TASK-002**: Implement `LoadPublicKey(pemData []byte) (*rsa.PublicKey, error)` in `pkg/picod/crypto.go`\n21:   - Parse PEM block from data\n22:   - Delegate to ParsePEM for key extraction\n23:   - Return error if PEM parsing fails\n24: \n25: - [ ] **TASK-003**: Implement `LoadPublicKeyFromBase64(base64PEM string) (*rsa.PublicKey, error)` in `pkg/picod/crypto.go`\n26:   - Decode base64 string to bytes\n27:   - Call LoadPublicKey with decoded bytes\n28:   - Handle base64 decoding errors\n29: \n30: - [ ] **TASK-004**: Implement `ParsePEM(pemBlock *pem.Block) (*rsa.PublicKey, error)` in `pkg/picod/crypto.go`\n31:   - Handle PKIX format (x509.ParsePKIXPublicKey)\n32:   - Handle PKCS#1 format (x509.ParsePKCS1PublicKey)\n33:   - Return error for unsupported formats\n34: \n35: - [ ] **TASK-005**: Implement `GenerateKeyPair(bits int) (*rsa.PrivateKey, *rsa.PublicKey, error)` in `pkg/picod/crypto.go`\n36:   - Generate RSA key pair using rsa.GenerateKey\n37:   - Return private and public keys\n38:   - Use crypto/rand for secure random generation\n39: \n40: ### Phase 2: JWT Claims & Validation (`jwt.go`)\n41: \n42: - [ ] **TASK-010**: Define `Claims` struct in `pkg/picod/jwt.go`\n43:   - Fields: `Sub` (string), `Iss` (string), `Aud` (string), `Exp` (int64), `Iat` (int64), `SandboxID` (string), `Namespace` (string)\n44:   - JSON tags for all fields\n45: \n46: - [ ] **TASK-011**: Implement `Validate(c *Claims, now time.Time, clockSkew time.Duration) error` in `pkg/picod/jwt.go`\n47:   - Check expiration (exp + clockSkew < now → expired)\n48:   - Check not before (iat - clockSkew > now → not yet valid)\n49:   - Validate required claims (sub, iss, aud, exp, iat present)\n50:   - Return appropriate error for each validation failure\n51: \n52: - [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `ParseAndValidate(tokenString string, publicKey *rsa.PublicKey, clockSkew time.Duration) (*Claims, error)` in `pkg/picod/jwt.go`\n53:   - Split token into header.payload.signature\n54:   - Verify signature using VerifySignature\n55:   - Parse payload JSON into Claims\n56:   - Validate claims using Validate\n57:   - Return parsed claims or error\n58: \n59: - [ ] **TASK-013**: Implement `VerifySignature(tokenString string, publicKey *rsa.PublicKey) error` in `pkg/picod/jwt.go`\n60:   - Decode header and payload (base64url)\n61:   - Decode signature (base64url)\n62:   - Construct signing input: `header.payload`\n63:   - Verify RSA-PKCS1v15 signature (SHA256)\n64:   - Return error if signature invalid\n65: \n66: ### Phase 3: Authentication Errors (`errors.go`)\n67: \n68: - [ ] **TASK-020**: Define `AuthErrorType` type and constants in `pkg/picod/errors.go`\n69:   - Type: `AuthErrorType` (string alias)\n70:   - Constants: `AuthErrorMissingToken`, `AuthErrorInvalidToken`, `AuthErrorExpiredToken`, `AuthErrorInvalidSig`, `AuthErrorInvalidClaims`, `AuthErrorInternal`\n71: \n72: - [ ] **TASK-021**: Define `AuthError` struct in `pkg/picod/errors.go`\n73:   - Fields: `Type` (AuthErrorType), `Message` (string), `Underlying` (error)\n74:   - Methods: `Error() string`, `Unwrap() error`\n75: \n76: - [ ] **TASK-022**: Implement `HTTPStatus(e *AuthError) int` in `pkg/picod/errors.go`\n77:   - Map error types to HTTP status codes:\n78:     - MissingToken, InvalidToken, InvalidSig, InvalidClaims → 401\n79:     - ExpiredToken → 401\n80:     - Internal → 500\n81: \n82: - [ ] **TASK-023**: Implement `NewAuthError(authType AuthErrorType, message string, underlying error) *AuthError` in `pkg/picod/errors.go`\n83:   - Constructor for AuthError\n84:   - Format message with context\n85: \n86: ### Phase 4: HTTP Middleware (`middleware.go`)\n87: \n88: - [ ] **TASK-030**: Define `JWTMiddleware` struct in `pkg/picod/middleware.go`\n89:   - Fields: `publicKey` (*rsa.PublicKey), `skipPaths` (map[string]bool), `clockSkew` (time.Duration), `logger` (klog.Logger)\n90: \n91: - [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement `NewJWTMiddleware(publicKey *rsa.PublicKey, clockSkew time.Duration, skipPaths ...string) *JWTMiddleware` in `pkg/picod/middleware.go`\n92:   - Initialize skipPaths map\n93:   - Set default clockSkew (30 seconds if 0)\n94:   - Create structured logger\n95: \n96: - [ ] **TASK-032**: Implement `Middleware(m *JWTMiddleware, next http.Handler) http.Handler` in `pkg/picod/middleware.go`\n97:   - Wrap handler with authentication logic\n98:   - Extract path from request\n99:   - Check if path should skip auth\n100:   - Extract token from Authorization header\n101:   - Validate token\n102:   - Call next handler on success, return error on failure\n103: \n104: - [ ] **TASK-033**: Implement `extractToken(m *JWTMiddleware, r *http.Request) (string, error)` in `pkg/picod/middleware.go`\n105:   - Get Authorization header\n106:   - Validate \"Bearer \" prefix\n107:   - Extract token string\n108:   - Return error if missing or malformed\n109: \n110: - [ ] **TASK-034**: Implement `shouldSkip(m *JWTMiddleware, path string) bool` in `pkg/picod/middleware.go`\n111:   - Check if path exists in skipPaths map\n112:   - Support exact path matching\n113: \n114: ### Phase 5: HTTP Response Helpers (`middleware.go`)\n115: \n116: - [ ] **TASK-040**: Implement `WriteJSON(w http.ResponseWriter, status int, data interface{})` in `pkg/picod/middleware.go`\n117:   - Set Content-Type header\n118:   - Set status code\n119:   - Encode data as JSON\n120:   - Handle encoding errors\n121: \n122: - [ ] **TASK-041**: Implement `WriteAuthError(w http.ResponseWriter, err *AuthError)` in `pkg/picod/middleware.go`\n123:   - Get HTTP status from error\n124:   - Write JSON error response\n125:   - Include error type and message\n126: \n127: - [ ] **TASK-042**: Define `HealthResponse` struct in `pkg/picod/middleware.go`\n128:   - Fields: `Status` (string), `Timestamp` (time.Time), `SandboxID` (string)\n129:   - JSON tags for all fields\n130: \n131: ### Phase 6: Configuration (`config.go`)\n132: \n133: - [ ] **TASK-050**: Add auth fields to `Config` struct in `pkg/picod/config.go`\n134:   - Fields: `AuthMode` (string), `PublicKeyPEM` (string), `SkipPaths` ([]string), `ClockSkew` (time.Duration)\n135: \n136: - [ ] **TASK-051**: Update `LoadConfig()` in `pkg/picod/config.go`\n137:   - Load `PICOD_AUTH_MODE` (default: \"none\")\n138:   - Load `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` (required if AuthMode=picod)\n139:   - Load `PICOD_AUTH_SKIP_PATHS` (default: \"/health\", comma-separated)\n140:   - Load `PICOD_AUTH_CLOCK_SKEW` (default: 30s)\n141: \n142: - [ ] **TASK-052**: Add command-line flag parsing helpers in `pkg/picod/config.go`\n143:   - `ParseAuthFlags()` function\n144:   - Flags: `-auth`, `-public-key`, `-skip-paths`, `-clock-skew`\n145:   - Merge flags with environment variables (flags take precedence)\n146: \n147: - [ ] **TASK-053**: Implement `Validate(c *Config) error` for auth config in `pkg/picod/config.go`\n148:   - If AuthMode=\"picod\", require PublicKeyPEM\n149:   - Validate clockSkew is non-negative\n150:   - Parse and validate skip paths\n151: \n152: ### Phase 7: PicoD Integration (`picod.go`)\n153: \n154: - [ ] **TASK-060**: Add `authMode` and `publicKey` fields to `PicoD` struct in `pkg/picod/picod.go`\n155:   - Fields: `authMode` (string), `publicKey` (*rsa.PublicKey)\n156: \n157: - [ ] **TASK-061**: Add `WithAuthMode(mode string) Option` in `pkg/picod/picod.go`\n158:   - Functional option to set auth mode\n159: \n160: - [ ] **TASK-062**: Add `WithPublicKey(pem string) Option` in `pkg/picod/picod.go`\n161:   - Functional option to set public key\n162:   - Load key from PEM\n163: \n164: - [ ] **TASK-063**: Implement `SetupHTTPServer(picod *PicoD, config *Config) (*http.Server, error)` in `pkg/picod/picod.go`\n165:   - Create ServeMux\n166:   - Register handlers\n167:   - Apply JWT middleware if AuthMode=picod\n168:   - Configure ReadHeaderTimeout (10s)\n169: \n170: ### Phase 8: Unit Tests\n171: \n172: #### Crypto Tests\n173: \n174: - [ ] **TEST-001**: Create `TestLoadPublicKey_Success` in `pkg/picod/crypto_test.go`\n175:   - Load valid PKIX PEM key\n176:   - Verify key returned without error\n177: \n178: - [ ] **TEST-002**: Create `TestLoadPublicKeyFromBase64` in `pkg/picod/crypto_test.go`\n179:   - Load base64-encoded PEM key\n180:   - Verify decoded key matches direct load\n181: \n182: - [ ] **TEST-003**: Create `TestLoadPublicKey_InvalidPEM` in `pkg/picod/crypto_test.go`\n183:   - Load invalid PEM data\n184:   - Verify error returned\n185: \n186: - [ ] **TEST-004**: Create `TestGenerateKeyPair` in `pkg/picod/crypto_test.go`\n187:   - Generate key pair (2048 bits)\n188:   - Verify private and public keys not nil\n189: \n190: #### JWT Tests\n191: \n192: - [ ] **TEST-010**: Create `TestClaims_Validate_Success` in `pkg/picod/jwt_test.go`\n193:   - Valid claims with future exp\n194:   - Verify no error\n195: \n196: - [ ] **TEST-011**: Create `TestClaims_Validate_Expired` in `pkg/picod/jwt_test.go`\n197:   - Claims with past exp\n198:   - Verify error returned\n199: \n200: - [ ] **TEST-012**: Create `TestClaims_Validate_Future` in `pkg/picod/jwt_test.go`\n201:   - Claims with future iat\n202:   - Verify error returned\n203: \n204: - [ ] **TEST-013**: Create `TestClaims_Validate_MissingClaims` in `pkg/picod/jwt_test.go`\n205:   - Claims missing required fields\n206:   - Verify error returned\n207: \n208: - [ ] **TEST-014**: Create `TestParseAndValidate_Success` in `pkg/picod/jwt_test.go`\n209:   - Generate valid token with test key\n210:   - Parse and validate\n211:   - Verify claims extracted correctly\n212: \n213: - [ ] **TEST-015**: Create `TestParseAndValidate_InvalidSignature` in `pkg/picod/jwt_test.go`\n214:   - Tamper with token signature\n215:   - Verify signature verification fails\n216: \n217: - [ ] **TEST-016**: Create `TestVerifySignature_RS256` in `pkg/picod/jwt_test.go`\n218:   - Verify RS256 signature algorithm\n219:   - Test with known token\n220: \n221: #### Error Tests\n222: \n223: - [ ] **TEST-020**: Create `TestAuthError_ErrorTypes` in `pkg/picod/errors_test.go`\n224:   - Verify all error types defined\n225:   - Verify Error() method works\n226: \n227: - [ ] **TEST-021**: Create `TestAuthError_HTTPStatus` in `pkg/picod/errors_test.go`\n228:   - Each error type maps to correct HTTP status\n229:   - 401 for auth errors, 500 for internal\n230: \n231: #### Middleware Tests\n232: \n233: - [ ] **TEST-030**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_ValidToken` in `pkg/picod/middleware_test.go`\n234:   - Request with valid JWT token\n235:   - Verify next handler called\n236:   - Verify request passes through\n237: \n238: - [ ] **TEST-031**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_MissingToken` in `pkg/picod/middleware_test.go`\n239:   - Request without Authorization header\n240:   - Verify 401 returned\n241:   - Verify next handler not called\n242: \n243: - [ ] **TEST-032**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_InvalidToken` in `pkg/picod/middleware_test.go`\n244:   - Request with malformed token\n245:   - Verify 401 returned\n246: \n247: - [ ] **TEST-033**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_ExpiredToken` in `pkg/picod/middleware_test.go`\n248:   - Request with expired token\n249:   - Verify 401 returned\n250: \n251: - [ ] **TEST-034**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_SkipPath` in `pkg/picod/middleware_test.go`\n252:   - Request to /health (skipped path)\n253:   - Verify auth not required\n254:   - Verify next handler called\n255: \n256: - [ ] **TEST-035**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_InvalidAuthHeader` in `pkg/picod/middleware_test.go`\n257:   - Request with non-Bearer auth scheme\n258:   - Verify 401 returned\n259: \n260: - [ ] **TEST-036**: Create `TestExtractToken` in `pkg/picod/middleware_test.go`\n261:   - Valid Bearer header → token extracted\n262:   - Missing header → error\n263:   - Malformed header → error\n264: \n265: #### Config Tests\n266: \n267: - [ ] **TEST-040**: Create `TestLoadConfig_AuthConfig` in `pkg/picod/config_test.go`\n268:   - Load auth config from environment\n269:   - Verify defaults applied\n270: \n271: - [ ] **TEST-041**: Create `TestConfig_Validate_AuthMode` in `pkg/picod/config_test.go`\n272:   - AuthMode=picod without key → error\n273:   - AuthMode=picod with key → valid\n274:   - AuthMode=none → valid\n275: \n276: ### Phase 9: Integration Tests\n277: \n278: - [ ] **TEST-050**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_Integration_FullFlow` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n279:   - Start real HTTP server with JWT middleware\n280:   - Make request with valid token\n281:   - Verify 200 OK\n282:   - Make request without token\n283:   - Verify 401 Unauthorized\n284: \n285: - [ ] **TEST-051**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_Integration_MultipleRequests` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n286:   - Concurrent requests with valid tokens\n287:   - Verify all succeed\n288:   - Verify no race conditions (run with -race)\n289: \n290: - [ ] **TEST-052**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_Integration_HealthEndpoint` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n291:   - Health endpoint without token → 200 OK\n292:   - Protected endpoint without token → 401\n293:   - Verify skip paths work in real server\n294: \n295: - [ ] **TEST-053**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_Integration_TokenTampering` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n296:   - Modify valid token payload\n297:   - Verify signature check fails\n298:   - Verify 401 returned\n299: \n300: - [ ] **TEST-054**: Create `TestSetupHTTPServer_Integration` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n301:   - Full server setup with auth enabled\n302:   - Verify middleware applied\n303:   - Verify server responds correctly\n304: \n305: ### Phase 10: Documentation\n306: \n307: - [ ] **DOC-001**: Add Go doc comments to all public types in `crypto.go`, `jwt.go`, `errors.go`, `middleware.go`\n308:   - Include parameter descriptions\n309:   - Include return value descriptions\n310:   - Include error conditions\n311: \n312: - [ ] **DOC-002**: Add usage examples in doc comments\n313:   - Example: creating JWT middleware\n314:   - Example: loading public key\n315:   - Example: validating token\n316: \n317: - [ ] **DOC-003**: Update `pkg/picod/README.md`\n318:   - Document JWT authentication\n319:   - Include configuration options\n320:   - Include token format requirements\n321:   - Include error handling guide\n322: \n323: - [ ] **DOC-004**: Add security documentation\n324:   - RSA key management best practices\n325:   - Token lifetime recommendations\n326:   - Clock skew considerations\n327:   - Key rotation strategy\n328: \n329: ## Acceptance Criteria\n330: \n331: - [ ] JWT middleware correctly validates tokens with RSA signatures\n332: - [ ] Invalid/missing tokens return 401 Unauthorized\n333: - [ ] Expired tokens are rejected\n334: - [ ] Signature verification works with RSA public key (PKIX and PKCS#1 formats)\n335: - [ ] Configurable skip paths work correctly\n336: - [ ] Health endpoint can be protected or public\n337: - [ ] Claims are correctly parsed and validated (exp, iat, sub, iss, aud)\n338: - [ ] Clock skew tolerance is configurable\n339: - [ ] Error types map to appropriate HTTP status codes\n340: - [ ] All unit tests pass\n341: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n342: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n343: - [ ] Documentation includes usage examples\n344: - [ ] Compatible with standard JWT libraries (PyJWT, node-jose, etc.)\n345: - [ ] RS256 (RSA-PKCS1v15 with SHA256) signature algorithm implemented\n346: \n347: ## Dependencies\n348: \n349: | Dependency | Source | Usage |\n350: |------------|--------|-------|\n351: | `crypto/rsa` | Standard | RSA signature verification |\n352: | `crypto/x509` | Standard | X.509 key parsing |\n353: | `crypto/rand` | Standard | Key generation |\n354: | `encoding/pem` | Standard | PEM decoding |\n355: | `encoding/base64` | Standard | Base64 decoding |\n356: | `encoding/json` | Standard | JSON claims parsing |\n357: | `net/http` | Standard | HTTP middleware |\n358: | `strings` | Standard | String manipulation |\n359: | `time` | Standard | Token time validation |\n360: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | External | Structured logging |\n361: | AR-015 (PicoD Command Execution API) | Completed | Base infrastructure |\n362: | AR-016 (PicoD File Management API) | Completed | Base infrastructure |\n363: \n364: ## Implementation Order\n365: \n366: ```\n367: TASK-001 → TASK-005 (Crypto utilities)\n368:     ↓\n369: TASK-010 → TASK-013 (JWT claims & validation)\n370:     ↓\n371: TASK-020 → TASK-023 (Auth errors)\n372:     ↓\n373: TASK-030 → TASK-034 (HTTP middleware)\n374:     ↓\n375: TASK-040 → TASK-042 (Response helpers)\n376:     ↓\n377: TASK-050 → TASK-053 (Configuration)\n378:     ↓\n379: TASK-060 → TASK-063 (PicoD integration)\n380:     ↓\n381: TEST-001 → TEST-041 (Unit tests)\n382:     ↓\n383: TEST-050 → TEST-054 (Integration tests)\n384:     ↓\n385: DOC-001 → DOC-004 (Documentation)\n386: ```\n387: \n388: ## Test Infrastructure\n389: \n390: - [ ] **TEST-060**: Create `generateTestToken(privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey, claims *Claims) (string, error)` helper in `pkg/picod/jwt_test.go`\n391:   - Create JWT header (RS256)\n392:   - Encode claims as JSON\n393:   - Sign with private key\n394:   - Return complete token\n395: \n396: - [ ] **TEST-061**: Create `testClaims() *Claims` helper in `pkg/picod/jwt_test.go`\n397:   - Return standard test claims with valid timestamps\n398: \n399: - [ ] **TEST-062**: Create `generateTestKeyPair() (*rsa.PrivateKey, *rsa.PublicKey, error)` helper in `pkg/picod/crypto_test.go`\n400:   - Generate RSA key pair for tests\n401:   - Use smaller key size (1024 bits) for speed\n402: \n403: - [ ] **TEST-063**: Create `newTestServer(handler http.Handler) (*httptest.Server, error)` helper in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n404:   - Create test HTTP server\n405:   - Return server and cleanup function\n406: \n407: ## Coverage Verification\n408: \n409: - [ ] **COV-001**: Run coverage check\n410:   - Command: `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/picod/... ./pkg/picod/...`\n411:   - Verify code coverage >= 80%\n412:   - Verify crypto.go, jwt.go, errors.go, middleware.go all covered\n413:   - Verify each .go file has corresponding _test.go file\n414: \n415: ## Security Considerations\n416: \n417: - [ ] **SEC-001**: Verify RSA signature uses SHA256 (RS256)\n418: - [ ] **SEC-002**: Verify clock skew prevents replay attacks\n419: - [ ] **SEC-003**: Verify token parsing rejects malformed input\n420: - [ ] **SEC-004**: Verify key loading rejects invalid formats\n421: - [ ] **SEC-005**: Verify error messages don't leak sensitive info\n\n(End of file - total 421 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-017 — PicoD JWT Middleware Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件 |\n| Module | `pkg/picod` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S |\n| Stage | ST-3 completed |\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: RSA Key Handling (`crypto.go`)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Create `pkg/picod/crypto.go`\n  - Define package-level imports: `crypto/rsa`, `crypto/x509`, `encoding/pem