n512: DOC-001 → DOC-003 (Documentation)\n513:     ↓\n514: BUILD-001 → BUILD-003 (Build config)\n515: ```\n516: \n517: ## Coverage Verification\n518: \n519: - [ ] **COV-001**: Run coverage check\n520:   - Command: `pytest --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing tests/`\n521:   - Verify code coverage >= 80%\n522:   - Verify all .py files have corresponding test_*.py files\n523:   - Verify main logic paths covered\n524: \n525: ## File Structure\n526: \n527: ```\n528: cmd/cli/\n529: ├── pyproject.toml\n530: ├── README.md\n531: ├── agentcube/\n532: │   ├── __init__.py\n533: │   ├── cli/\n534: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n535: │   │   └── main.py\n536: │   ├── models/\n537: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n538: │   │   └── pack_models.py\n539: │   ├── runtime/\n540: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n541: │   │   ├── pack_runtime.py\n542: │   │   ├── build_runtime.py\n543: │   │   ├── publish_runtime.py\n544: │   │   ├── invoke_runtime.py\n545: │   │   └── status_runtime.py\n546: │   ├── services/\n547: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n548: │   │   ├── metadata_service.py\n549: │   │   ├── docker_service.py\n550: │   │   ├── k8s_provider.py\n551: │   │   └── agentcube_provider.py\n552: │   └── operations/\n553: │       └── __init__.py\n554: ├── examples/\n555: │   ├── hello-agent/\n556: │   │   ├── main.py\n557: │   │   └── requirements.txt\n558: │   └── math-agent/\n559: │       ├── main.py\n560: │       └── requirements.txt\n561: └── tests/\n562:     ├── __init__.py\n563:     ├── conftest.py\n564:     ├── test_pack_runtime.py\n565:     ├── test_metadata_service.py\n566:     └── fixtures/\n567:         ├── __init__.py\n568:         ├── valid_python_agent/\n569:         │   ├── main.py\n570:         │   └── requirements.txt\n571:         └── valid_java_agent/\n572:             ├── pom.xml\n573:             └── src/main/java/App.java\n574: ```\n575: \n576: ## Command Reference\n577: \n578: ### pack Command\n579: \n580: ```bash\n581: kubectl-agentcube pack [OPTIONS]\n582: \n583: Options:\n584:   -f, --workspace PATH          Path to agent workspace directory [default: .]\n585:   --agent-name TEXT             Override agent name\n586:   --language TEXT               Programming language (python, java)\n587:   --entrypoint TEXT             Override entrypoint command\n588:   --port INTEGER                Port to expose in Dockerfile\n589:   --build-mode TEXT             Build strategy: local or cloud\n590:   --description TEXT            Agent description\n591:   --output PATH                 Output path for packaged workspace\n592:   --verbose                     Enable detailed logging\n593:   --help                        Show this message and exit\n594: ```\n595: \n596: ### Global Options\n597: \n598: ```bash\n599: kubectl-agentcube [OPTIONS] COMMAND [ARGS]\n600: \n601: Options:\n602:   --version                     Show version and exit\n603:   -v, --verbose                 Enable verbose output\n604:   --help                        Show this message and exit\n605: ```\n606: \n607: ### Example Usage\n608: \n609: ```bash\n610: # Pack Python agent with defaults\n611: kubectl-agentcube pack -f /path/to/agent\n612: \n613: # Pack with custom options\n614: kubectl-agentcube pack \\\n615:   --agent-name my-agent \\\n616:   --language python \\\n617:   --entrypoint \"python main.py\" \\\n618:   --port 8080 \\\n619:   --build-mode local \\\n620:   --output /tmp/packaged-agent\n621: \n622: # Pack with verbose output\n623: kubectl-agentcube pack -f ./my-agent --verbose\n624: ```\n625: \n626: ## Testing Strategy\n627: \n628: ### Unit Tests\n629: \n630: 1. **PackRuntime Tests**: Validate packaging logic, workspace validation, metadata handling\n631: 2. **MetadataService Tests**: Validate metadata loading, saving, validation\n632: 3. **Model Tests**: Validate Pydantic validators and dataclass behavior\n633: \n634: ### Integration Tests\n635: \n636: 1. **test_pack_hello_agent**: Full pack flow with hello-agent example\n637: 2. **test_pack_math_agent**: Full pack flow with math-agent example\n638: 3. **test_pack_with_output_path**: Pack with custom output path\n639: 4. **test_pack_java_agent**: Pack Java workspace (when fixture available)\n640: \n641: ### Test Fixtures\n642: \n643: - `valid_python_agent/`: Python workspace with main.py and requirements.txt\n644: - `valid_java_agent/`: Java workspace with pom.xml and src/\n\n(End of file - total 644 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-020 — CLI Pack Command Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-020 — CLI pack 命令 |\n| Module | `cmd/cli` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-3 completed |\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Package Structure Setup\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Create `cmd/cli/pyproject.toml`\n  - Define build system (setuptools>=61.0, wheel)\n  - Set project metadata (name, version, description, license, authors)\n  - Specify Python requirement (>=3.10)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-020/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775866725378,"end":1775866725391}}}}
