{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775866857615,"sessionID":"ses_28618bf6dffeGAxAQ8WcrcDRZ1","part":{"id":"prt_d79e7d4e200155TRiQtEwRpn5C","messageID":"msg_d79e7c4480015pgESjhVvcM9eS","sessionID":"ses_28618bf6dffeGAxAQ8WcrcDRZ1","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_83d398f9395842eb90f5b85d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-021/tasks.md","content":"# AR-021 — CLI Build Command Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-021 — CLI build 命令 |\n| Module | `cmd/cli` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-3 completed |\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: BuildRuntime Implementation (`agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Update `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` - Add package imports\n  - Define imports: `logging`, `re`, `pathlib.Path`, `typing.Any, Dict, Optional`\n  - Import `AgentMetadata`, `MetadataService` from `agentcube.services.metadata_service`\n  - Import `DockerService` from `agentcube.services.docker_service`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-002**: Implement `BuildRuntime.__init__(self, verbose: bool = False)` in `build_runtime.py`\n  - Initialize `self.verbose = verbose`\n  - Configure logging if verbose\n  - Initialize `self.metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)`\n  - Initialize `self.docker_service = DockerService(verbose=verbose)`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-003**: Implement `BuildRuntime.build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]` in `build_runtime.py`\n  - Log build start\n  - Load metadata from workspace\n  - Validate build prerequisites\n  - Store original version for rollback\n  - Increment version\n  - Try/except block for build with version rollback on failure\n  - Determine build mode (local vs cloud)\n  - Call `_build_local` or `_build_cloud`\n  - Update build metadata on success\n  - Return result dict\n\n- [ ] **TASK-004**: Implement `BuildRuntime._increment_version(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str` in `build_runtime.py`\n  - Parse semver version using regex\n  - Handle patch increment (1.2.3 → 1.2.4)\n  - Handle pre-release versions (1.0.0-alpha.1 → 1.0.0-alpha.2)\n  - Handle non-semver fallback (v1.0 → v1.0.1)\n  - Handle missing version (default to 0.1.0)\n  - Save updated metadata\n  - Log and return new version\n\n- [ ] **TASK-005**: Implement `BuildRuntime._validate_build_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None` in `build_runtime.py`\n  - Check Dockerfile exists in workspace\n  - Raise `ValueError(\"Dockerfile not found in workspace\")` if missing\n  - Call `docker_service.check_docker_available()`\n  - Raise `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")` if unavailable\n\n- [ ] **TASK-006**: Implement `BuildRuntime._build_local(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]` in `build_runtime.py`\n  - Construct dockerfile_path\n  - Construct image_name with version\n  - Extract proxy from options\n  - Build build_args dict with HTTP_PROXY/HTTPS_PROXY if proxy provided\n  - Call `docker_service.build_image()` with required params\n  - Add image_name to result\n  - Return result dict\n\n- [ ] **TASK-007**: Implement `BuildRuntime._build_cloud(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]` in `build_runtime.py`\n  - Extract cloud_provider from options (default: \"huawei\")\n  - Validate cloud provider is supported\n  - Raise `ValueError(f\"Unsupported cloud provider: {cloud_provider}\")` if not\n  - Log cloud build start\n  - Return placeholder result dict with cloud-specific image_name\n\n- [ ] **TASK-008**: Implement `BuildRuntime._update_build_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, build_result: Dict[str, str])` in `build_runtime.py`\n  - Initialize metadata.image dict if None\n  - Update metadata.image with build_result\n  - Save metadata via metadata_service\n\n### Phase 2: DockerService Implementation (`agentcube/services/docker_service.py`)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-010**: Update `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` - Add package imports\n  - Define imports: `logging`, `time`, `pathlib.Path`, `typing.Any, Dict, Optional`\n  - Import `docker` from docker package\n  - Import `DockerException` from docker.errors\n\n- [ ] **TASK-011**: Implement `DockerService.__init__(self, verbose: bool = False)` in `docker_service.py`\n  - Initialize `self.verbose = verbose`\n  - Configure logging if verbose\n  - Initialize `self._client: Optional[docker.DockerClient] = None`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `DockerService.client` property in `docker_service.py`\n  - Create docker client via `docker.from_env()` if None\n  - Return client\n\n- [ ] **TASK-013**: Implement `DockerService.check_docker_available(self) -> bool` in `docker_service.py`\n  - Try to ping docker client\n  - Return True on success\n  - Catch DockerException, log warning, return False\n\n- [ ] **TASK-014**: Implement `DockerService.build_image(self, dockerfile_path: Path, context_path: Path, image_name: str, tag: str = \"latest\", build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Dict[str, str]` in `docker_service.py`\n  - Check docker availability first\n  - Log build start\n  - Call `client.images.build()` with path, dockerfile, tag, buildargs, rm, forcerm\n  - Get image info via `get_image_info()`\n  - Add build_time to result\n  - Return result dict\n  - Catch DockerException and raise RuntimeError\n\n- [ ] **TASK-015**: Implement `DockerService.get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]` in `docker_service.py`\n  - Get image via `client.images.get()`\n  - Extract image_id from attrs[\"Id\"]\n  - Extract size from attrs[\"Size\"]\n  - Format size using `_format_size()`\n  - Return dict with image_name, image_id, image_size, size_bytes\n  - Catch DockerException and return empty dict\n\n- [ ] **TASK-016**: Implement `DockerService._format_size(self, size_bytes: int) -> str` in `docker_service.py`\n  - Convert bytes to human-readable format\n  - Iterate through [\"B\", \"KB\", \"MB\", \"GB\"]\n  - Return formatted string (e.g., \"125.50 MB\")\n\n- [ ] **TASK-017**: Implement `DockerService.push_image(self, image_name: str, registry_url: Optional[str] = None, username: Optional[str] = None, password: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, str]` in `docker_service.py`\n  - Check docker availability\n  - Tag image if registry_url provided\n  - Login if username and password provided\n  - Push image with streaming\n  - Check for errors in push logs\n  - Log progress if verbose\n  - Return dict with pushed_image, push_time\n  - Catch DockerException and raise RuntimeError\n\n- [ ] **TASK-018**: Implement `DockerService._docker_login_sdk(self, registry: Optional[str], username: str, password: str) -> None` in `docker_service.py`\n  - Call `client.login()` with credentials\n  - Log success\n  - Catch DockerException and raise RuntimeError\n\n- [ ] **TASK-019**: Implement `DockerService._tag_image_sdk(self, source_image: str, target_image: str) -> None` in `docker_service.py`\n  - Get source image\n  - Call `image.tag()` with target_image\n  - Log success\n  - Catch DockerException and raise RuntimeError\n\n- [ ] **TASK-020**: Implement `DockerService.remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool` in `docker_service.py`\n  - Call `client.images.remove()` with force=True\n  - Log success\n  - Return True\n  - Catch DockerException, log warning, return False\n\n### Phase 3: CLI Build Command (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-030**: Update `agentcube/cli/main.py` - Import BuildRuntime\n  - Add import: `from agentcube.runtime.build_runtime import BuildRuntime`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement `build()` command in `main.py` with Typer decorator\n  - Define function with `@app.command()` decorator\n  - Accept `workspace` option (-f, --workspace, default \".\")\n  - Accept `proxy` option (-p, --proxy, Optional[str])\n  - Accept `cloud_provider` option (--cloud-provider, Optional[str])\n  - Accept `output` option (--output, Optional[str])\n  - Accept `verbose` option (--verbose, bool, default False)\n  - Add docstring for command help\n\n- [ ] **TASK-032**: Implement `build()` command body in `main.py`\n  - Configure logging if verbose\n  - Instantiate `BuildRuntime(verbose=verbose)`\n  - Resolve workspace_path\n  - Show progress spinner with Rich\n  - Build options dict with proxy, cloud_provider, output\n  - Call `runtime.build(workspace_path, **options)`\n  - Update progress on completion\n  - Print success message with image_name, image_id, image_size\n  - Handle errors with `_handle_error()`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-033**: Update `_handle_error()` to support build command\n  - Ensure error messages include command context\n  - Print traceback if verbose\n\n- [ ] **TASK-034**: Add build time to success output\n  - Print `build_time` from result if available\n\n- [ ] **TASK-035**: Add next step guidance after build success\n  - Suggest `agentcube publish` command with appropriate flags\n\n### Phase 4: Cloud Provider Support (`agentcube/services/cloud_providers/`)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-040**: Create `agentcube/services/cloud_providers/__init__.py`\n  - Package marker with docstring\n  - Export provider classes\n\n- [ ] **TASK-041**: Create `agentcube/services/cloud_providers/base.py`\n  - Define `CloudProvider` abstract base class\n  - Define abstract methods: `build_image()`, `check_credentials()`, `get_build_status()`\n  - Define common constants and types\n\n- [ ] **TASK-042**: Create `agentcube/services/cloud_providers/huawei.py`\n  - Implement `HuaweiCloudProvider` class extending `CloudProvider`\n  - Implement `__init__(self, verbose: bool = False)`\n  - Implement `build_image()` - trigger Huawei Cloud Container Registry build\n  - Implement `check_credentials()` - validate Huawei Cloud credentials\n  - Implement `get_build_status()` - poll build status\n  - Handle timeout (default 600s)\n  - Raise `TimeoutError(\"Cloud build exceeded timeout\")` on timeout\n\n- [ ] **TASK-043**: Implement cloud provider factory in `agentcube/services/cloud_providers/__init__.py`\n  - Create `get_provider(name: str, verbose: bool = False) -> CloudProvider`\n  - Map provider names to classes\n  - Raise `ValueError(f\"Unsupported cloud provider: {name}\")` for unknown providers\n\n### Phase 5: Proxy Configuration Support\n\n- [ ] **TASK-050**: Add proxy environment variable fallback in `build_runtime.py`\n  - Check for `HTTP_PROXY` or `HTTPS_PROXY` env vars if no `-p` flag\n  - Use env var as proxy value\n\n- [ ] **TASK-051**: Document proxy support for pip installs in `_build_local()`\n  - Add comment for future enhancement: pass proxy to pip via build args\n\n- [ ] **TASK-052**: Document proxy support for maven builds in `_build_local()`\n  - Add comment for future enhancement: generate settings.xml with proxy\n\n### Phase 6: Build Validation Prerequisites\n\n- [ ] **TASK-060**: Implement image name validation in `_validate_build_prerequisites()`\n  - Sanitize agent_name per Docker naming rules\n  - Reject invalid characters\n  - Raise `ValueError(\"Invalid image name: {detail}\")` if invalid\n\n- [ ] **TASK-061**: Validate metadata in `_validate_build_prerequisites()`\n  - Verify `agent_metadata.yaml` exists and is valid YAML\n  - Raise `ValueError(\"Invalid metadata file\")` if parsing fails\n\n### Phase 7: Build Output and Reporting\n\n- [ ] **TASK-070**: Format build success output in `build()` command\n  - Print success checkmark\n  - Print Image: {image_name}:{tag}\n  - Print Image ID: {image_id}\n  - Print Size: {image_size}\n  - Print Build time: {build_time}s\n  - Use Rich formatting (cyan for values)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-071**: Implement verbose build log streaming\n  - If verbose, stream Docker build logs to console\n  - Use Rich for formatted output\n\n- [ ] **TASK-072**: Add next step guidance\n  - Print suggestion: \"Next: Run 'agentcube publish' to publish this image\"\n  - Include suggested command with image name\n\n### Phase 8: Unit Tests\n\n#### BuildRuntime Tests\n\n- [ ] **TEST-001**: Create `cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py`\n  - Define test imports (tempfile, pathlib, pytest, yaml)\n  - Define pytest fixture `python_workspace_with_dockerfile` that creates temp directory with main.py, requirements.txt, Dockerfile, agent_metadata.yaml\n\n- [ ] **TEST-002**: Implement `TestBuildRuntime.test_build_local_success` in `test_build_runtime.py`\n  - Create BuildRuntime\n  - Call build with python_workspace_with_dockerfile\n  - Verify result contains image_name, image_id, image_size, build_time\n  - Verify metadata updated with image info\n\n- [ ] **TEST-003**: Implement `TestBuildRuntime.test_build_missing_dockerfile` in `test_build_runtime.py`\n  - Call build with workspace without Dockerfile\n  - Verify ValueError raised with \"Dockerfile not found\" message\n\n- [ ] **TEST-004**: Implement `TestBuildRuntime.test_build_docker_unavailable` in `test_build_runtime.py`\n  - Mock docker_service.check_docker_available to return False\n  - Verify RuntimeError raised with \"Docker is not available\" message\n\n- [ ] **TEST-005**: Implement `TestBuildRuntime.test_build_version_increment` in `test_build_runtime.py`\n  - Create workspace with version 1.2.3\n  - Call build\n  - Verify version incremented to 1.2.4 in metadata\n\n- [ ] **TEST-006**: Implement `TestBuildRuntime.test_build_version_rollback_on_failure` in `test_build_runtime.py`\n  - Mock docker_service.build_image to raise exception\n  - Verify build fails\n  - Verify version reverted to original\n\n- [ ] **TEST-007**: Implement `TestBuildRuntime.test_build_cloud_mode` in `test_build_runtime.py`\n  - Call build with cloud_provider=\"huawei\"\n  - Verify cloud build path taken\n  - Verify result has cloud-specific image_name\n\n- [ ] **TEST-008**: Implement `TestBuildRuntime.test_build_unsupported_cloud_provider` in `test_build_runtime.py`\n  - Call build with cloud_provider=\"unknown\"\n  - Verify ValueError raised\n\n- [ ] **TEST-009**: Implement `TestBuildRuntime.test_build_proxy_configuration` in `test_build_runtime.py`\n  - Call build with proxy=\"http://proxy:port\"\n  - Verify build_args include HTTP_PROXY and HTTPS_PROXY\n\n- [ ] **TEST-010**: Implement `TestBuildRuntime.test_build_prerelease_version_increment` in `test_build_runtime.py`\n  - Create workspace with version 1.0.0-alpha.1\n  - Call build\n  - Verify version incremented to 1.0.0-alpha.2\n\n- [ ] **TEST-011**: Implement `TestBuildRuntime.test_build_non_semver_version` in `test_build_runtime.py`\n  - Create workspace with version \"v1.0\"\n  - Call build\n  - Verify version becomes \"v1.0.1\" or similar fallback\n\n#### DockerService Tests\n\n- [ ] **TEST-020**: Create `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n  - Define test imports\n\n- [ ] **TEST-021**: Implement `TestDockerService.test_check_docker_available_true` in `test_docker_service.py`\n  - Mock docker client ping to succeed\n  - Verify method returns True\n\n- [ ] **TEST-022**: Implement `TestDockerService.test_check_docker_available_false` in `test_docker_service.py`\n  - Mock docker client ping to raise DockerException\n  - Verify method returns False\n\n- [ ] **TEST-023**: Implement `TestDockerService.test_build_image_success` in `test_docker_service.py`\n  - Mock docker client images.build\n  - Call build_image\n  - Verify result contains expected fields\n\n- [ ] **TEST-024**: Implement `TestDockerService.test_build_image_docker_exception` in `test_docker_service.py`\n  - Mock docker client to raise DockerException\n  - Verify RuntimeError raised\n\n- [ ] **TEST-025**: Implement `TestDockerService.test_get_image_info` in `test_docker_service.py`\n  - Mock docker client images.get\n  - Verify image info extracted correctly\n\n- [ ] **TEST-026**: Implement `TestDockerService.test_format_size` in `test_docker_service.py`\n  - Test various byte sizes\n  - Verify human-readable format correct\n\n- [ ] **TEST-027**: Implement `TestDockerService.test_push_image_success` in `test_docker_service.py`\n  - Mock docker client push\n  - Verify push succeeds\n\n- [ ] **TEST-028**: Implement `TestDockerService.test_push_image_with_auth` in `test_docker_service.py`\n  - Mock docker login and push\n  - Verify credentials passed correctly\n\n- [ ] **TEST-029**: Implement `TestDockerService.test_remove_image` in `test_docker_service.py`\n  - Mock docker client remove\n  - Verify image removed\n\n#### CLI Build Command Tests\n\n- [ ] **TEST-030**: Create `cmd/cli/tests/test_build_command.py`\n  - Define test imports (typer.testing, subprocess)\n\n- [ ] **TEST-031**: Implement `TestBuildCommand.test_build_command_registered` in `test_build_command.py`\n  - Run `agentcube build --help`\n  - Verify command exists and shows help\n\n- [ ] **TEST-032**: Implement `TestBuildCommand.test_build_default_workspace` in `test_build_command.py`\n  - Run `agentcube build` in workspace with Dockerfile\n  - Verify build uses current directory\n\n- [ ] **TEST-033**: Implement `TestBuildCommand.test_build_custom_workspace` in `test_build_command.py`\n  - Run `agentcube build -f /path/to/workspace`\n  - Verify custom workspace used\n\n- [ ] **TEST-034**: Implement `TestBuildCommand.test_build_with_proxy` in `test_build_command.py`\n  - Run `agentcube build -p http://proxy:port`\n  - Verify proxy passed to build\n\n- [ ] **TEST-035**: Implement `TestBuildCommand.test_build_with_cloud_provider` in `test_build_command.py`\n  - Run `agentcube build --cloud-provider huawei`\n  - Verify cloud mode activated\n\n- [ ] **TEST-036**: Implement `TestBuildCommand.test_build_with_output` in `test_build_command.py`\n  - Run `agentcube build --output /path/to/output`\n  - Verify artifacts copied to output\n\n- [ ] **TEST-037**: Implement `TestBuildCommand.test_build_verbose_mode` in `test_build_command.py`\n  - Run `agentcube build --verbose`\n  - Verify debug logs displayed\n\n- [ ] **TEST-038**: Implement `TestBuildCommand.test_build_error_output` in `test_build_command.py`\n  - Run build in workspace without Dockerfile\n  - Verify error message displayed\n  - Verify exit code is 1\n\n### Phase 9: Integration Tests\n\n- [ ] **TEST-040**: Create `cmd/cli/tests/test_build_integration.py`\n  - Define integration test imports\n\n- [ ] **TEST-041**: Implement `test_build_hello_agent_integration` in `test_build_integration.py`\n  - Use examples/hello-agent workspace\n  - Run full pack → build flow\n  - Verify Docker image created\n  - Verify image can be inspected\n\n- [ ] **TEST-042**: Implement `test_build_math_agent_integration` in `test_build_integration.py`\n  - Use examples/math-agent workspace\n  - Run full pack → build flow\n  - Verify Docker image created with correct name/tag\n\n- [ ] **TEST-043**: Implement `test_build_with_proxy_integration` in `test_build_integration.py`\n  - Start test proxy server\n  - Run build with proxy\n  - Verify proxy used for dependency resolution (if testable)\n\n- [ ] **TEST-044**: Implement `test_build_version_persists_integration` in `test_build_integration.py`\n  - Build agent twice\n  - Verify version incremented each time\n  - Verify metadata reflects final version\n\n### Phase 10: Documentation\n\n- [ ] **DOC-001**: Add docstrings to BuildRuntime class and all methods\n  - Include parameter descriptions\n  - Include return value descriptions\n  - Include error conditions\n\n- [ ] **DOC-002**: Add docstrings to DockerService class and all methods\n  - Include parameter descriptions\n  - Include return value descriptions\n  - Include error conditions\n\n- [ ] **DOC-003**: Add docstrings to CloudProvider classes\n  - Document cloud provider interface\n  - Document Huawei Cloud implementation\n\n- [ ] **DOC-004**: Update `cmd/cli/README.md`\n  - Document build command\n  - Include usage examples\n  - Document cloud provider options\n  - Document proxy configuration\n\n- [ ] **DOC-005**: Create `cmd/cli/examples/README.md` section for build\n  - Document building example agents\n  - Include common troubleshooting\n\n### Phase 11: Error Codes and Exit Handling\n\n- [ ] **TASK-080**: Implement error exit codes in `build()` command\n  - Exit code 1 for all errors\n  - Ensure typer.Exit(1) raised on errors\n\n- [ ] **TASK-081**: Document error codes\n  - Docker unavailable → 1\n  - Missing Dockerfile → 1\n  - Invalid cloud provider → 1\n  - Build failure → 1\n  - Cloud build timeout → 1\n  - Version increment failure → 1\n\n### Phase 12: Coverage Verification\n\n- [ ] **COV-001**: Run coverage check\n  - Command: `pytest --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing tests/`\n  - Verify code coverage >= 80%\n  - Verify build_runtime.py, docker_service.py, main.py build command all covered\n  - Verify each .py file has corresponding test_*.py file\n  - Verify main logic paths covered\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `agentcube build` command registered and accessible\n- [ ] Build command accepts all specified options (-f, -p, --cloud-provider, --output, --verbose)\n- [ ] Default workspace resolves to current directory\n- [ ] Custom workspace path works (absolute and relative)\n- [ ] Proxy configuration passed to build\n- [ ] Cloud provider selection overrides to cloud mode\n- [ ] Output path for build artifacts supported\n- [ ] Verbose mode enables DEBUG logging\n- [ ] BuildRuntime instantiated with verbose flag\n- [ ] BuildRuntime.build() called with options dict\n- [ ] Exceptions handled with _handle_error()\n- [ ] Success message displayed with image details\n- [ ] Build mode resolution: local default, cloud with --cloud-provider\n- [ ] Cloud mode requires cloud provider name\n- [ ] Docker availability check before local build\n- [ ] Docker not available raises RuntimeError\n- [ ] DockerService.build_image() called with correct params\n- [ ] Image tagging convention: {agent_name}:{version}\n- [ ] Fallback tag: {agent_name}:latest when no version\n- [ ] Version increment: patch (1.2.3 → 1.2.4)\n- [ ] Pre-release version handling (1.0.0-alpha.1 → 1.0.0-alpha.2)\n- [ ] Version revert on build failure\n- [ ] Version string fallback for non-semver\n- [ ] Cloud build triggers cloud provider\n- [ ] Unsupported cloud provider raises ValueError\n- [ ] Dockerfile existence check\n- [ ] Missing Dockerfile raises ValueError\n- [ ] Metadata validation\n- [ ] Image name validation/sanitization\n- [ ] Build success output formatted with Rich\n- [ ] Build result updates agent_metadata.yaml\n- [ ] Verbose mode streams build logs\n- [ ] Next step guidance suggests publish command\n- [ ] Proxy from CLI flag or environment variable\n- [ ] Error exit codes all return 1\n- [ ] Unit tests achieve >= 80% code coverage\n- [ ] Integration tests pass\n- [ ] All error messages match spec\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Source | Usage |\n|------------|--------|-------|\n| `typer[all]` | External (>=0.9.0) | CLI framework |\n| `pydantic` | External (>=2.0.0) | Data validation |\n| `docker` | External (>=6.0.0) | Docker SDK |\n| `rich` | External (>=13.0.0) | Output formatting |\n| `semver` | External (>=3.0.0) | Version parsing |\n| `pyyaml` | External (>=6.0) | Metadata handling |\n| `pytest` | External (>=7.4.0) | Testing framework |\n| `pytest-asyncio` | External (>=0.21.0) | Async test support |\n| `pytest-cov` | External (>=4.1.0) | Coverage reporting |\n| `pytest-mock` | External (>=3.11.0) | Mocking utilities |\n| delta-spec-ar-021.md | Internal | Build command specification |\n| cli-toolkit/spec.md | Internal | CLI specification |\n| AR-020 (CLI pack command) | Completed | Base infrastructure |\n\n## Implementation Order\n\n```\nTASK-001 → TASK-009 (BuildRuntime core)\n    ↓\nTASK-010 → TASK-020 (DockerService)\n    ↓\nTASK-030 → TASK-035 (CLI build command)\n    ↓\nTASK-040 → TASK-043 (Cloud providers)\n    ↓\nTASK-050 → TASK-052 (Proxy support)\n    ↓\nTASK-060 → TASK-061 (Build validation)\n    ↓\nTASK-070 → TASK-072 (Output/reporting)\n    ↓\nTASK-080 → TASK-081 (Error codes)\n    ↓\nTEST-001 → TEST-029 (Unit tests)\n    ↓\nTEST-030 → TEST-038 (CLI command tests)\n    ↓\nTEST-040 → TEST-044 (Integration tests)\n    ↓\nDOC-001 → DOC-005 (Documentation)\n    ↓\nCOV-001 (Coverage verification)\n```\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\ncmd/cli/\n├── agentcube/\n│   ├── cli/\n│   │   └── main.py (updated with build command)\n│   ├── runtime/\n│   │   └── build_runtime.py (implemented)\n│   ├── services/\n│   │   ├── docker_service.py (implemented)\n│   │   └── cloud_providers/\n│   │       ├── __init__.py\n│   │       ├── base.py\n│   │       └── huawei.py\n│   └── models/\n│       └── pack_models.py (from AR-020)\n└── tests/\n    ├── test_build_runtime.py\n    ├── test_docker_service.py\n    ├── test_build_command.py\n    └── test_build_integration.py\n```\n\n## Command Reference\n\n### build Command\n\n```bash\nkubectl-agentcube build [OPTIONS]\n\nOptions:\n  -f, --workspace PATH          Path to agent workspace directory [default: .]\n  -p, --proxy TEXT              Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution\n  --cloud-provider TEXT         Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\n  --output PATH                 Output path for build artifacts\n  --verbose                     Enable detailed logging\n  --help                        Show this message and exit\n```\n\n### Example Usage\n\n```bash\n# Build with defaults (local Docker build)\nkubectl-agentcube build -f /path/to/agent\n\n# Build with proxy\nkubectl-agentcube build -f ./my-agent -p http://proxy.company.com:8080\n\n# Build in cloud (Huawei Cloud)\nkubectl-agentcube build -f ./my-agent --cloud-provider huawei\n\n# Build with custom output\nkubectl-agentcube build -f ./my-agent --output /tmp/build-output\n\n# Build with verbose logging\nkubectl-agentcube build -f ./my-agent --verbose\n\n# Full workflow: pack → build → publish\nkubectl-agentcube pack -f ./my-agent\nkubectl-agentcube build -f ./my-agent\nkubectl-agentcube publish -f ./my-agent\n```\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n1. **BuildRuntime Tests**: Validate build logic, version increment/rollback, mode resolution\n2. **DockerService Tests**: Validate Docker operations, image building, pushing\n3. **CLI Command Tests**: Validate CLI option parsing, error handling, output formatting\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n1. **test_build_hello_agent_integration**: Full pack → build flow with hello-agent\n2. **test_build_math_agent_integration**: Full pack → build flow with math-agent\n3. **test_build_with_proxy_integration**: Build with proxy configuration\n4. **test_build_version_persists_integration**: Version increment across builds\n\n### Test Fixtures\n\n- `python_workspace_with_dockerfile/`: Python workspace with Dockerfile, main.py, requirements.txt, agent_metadata.yaml\n- `python_workspace_no_dockerfile/`: Python workspace without Dockerfile\n- `mock_docker_client`: Mocked Docker client for unit tests\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n- [ ] **SEC-001**: Verify Docker daemon connection uses secure socket\n- [ ] **SEC-002**: Verify proxy credentials not logged in verbose mode\n- [ ] **SEC-003**: Verify cloud provider credentials handled securely\n- [ ] **SEC-004**: Verify error messages don't leak sensitive information\n- [ ] **SEC-005**: Verify image names sanitized to prevent injection attacks\n\n## Open Questions (from spec)\n\n1. Should build command support `--tag` override for custom image tags? (Future enhancement)\n2. Should multi-platform builds (`--platform`) be supported in initial release? (Future enhancement)\n3. Should build cache options (`--no-cache`, `--cache-from`) be exposed? (Future enhancement)\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py\">\nERROR [67:13] Argument of type \"float\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"value\" of type \"str\" in function \"__se